# iron-layer-dev-workspace — Workspace Overview

Centralized development workspace for the Exodus / Iron Layer platform team.
All AI configurations (Cursor rules, Claude skills, MCP server) and coding standards are managed here and synced into every active repo via `make sync-ai`.

## Workspace Layout (by layer)

```
Cursor Sidebar (layered groups):

── WORKSPACE ──────────────────────────────
  iron-layer-dev-workspace/    # This repo — orchestrator, AI configs, standards
    ai/cursor/rules/           # 16 .mdc files (canonical — edit here, not in repos)
    ai/cursor/skills/          # Cursor skills (canonical)
    ai/cursor/mcp.json.template # MCP config template
    ai/claude/CLAUDE.md        # Canonical CLAUDE.md
    ai/claude/skills/          # 8 Claude skills (canonical)
    ai/shared/AGENTS.md        # Canonical AGENTS.md
    development_docs/          # Architecture, backlog, design docs
    tooling/scripts/           # setup.sh, sync-ai-config.sh, check-env.sh
    standards/                 # ruff, sqlfluff, pre-commit configs
    workspace.yml              # Workspace manifest (repo list, tool pins)

── PRODUCTS ───────────────────────────────
  ironlayer_oss/               # IronLayer — SHIP (public, Apache 2.0)
  ironlayer_infra/             # Exodus Foundation — BUILD
  exodus-core/                 # Shared Kernel (depended on by Foundation + Autopilot)

── AGENTS ─────────────────────────────────
  exodus-autopilot/            # Exodus Autopilot — RUN

── CLIENTS & INFRA ────────────────────────
  exodus-client-template/      # Per-client config template
  exodus-terraform/            # GitHub org Terraform (all repos managed here)

── TOOLS ──────────────────────────────────
  Data-eXchange/               # Rust CLI — dx diff, dx validate, dx query

── REFERENCE (read-only) ──────────────────
  dpb-data-platform-in-a-box/  # Legacy monolith — agent code reference
  dpb-internal/                # Legacy review engine reference
  dpb-platform/                # Legacy framework reference
  AEGIS-DWH-IN-A-BOX-V2/      # Prototype reference
```

## Key Commands

```bash
# ─── Workspace management ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
make setup          # First-time setup: install tools, clone repos
make update         # Pull all repos + re-sync AI configs
make sync-ai        # Push AI configs from ai/ → all active repos
make check          # Verify env health: tools, env vars, repo access
make status         # Git status across all production repos
make lint           # Lint all Python repos (ruff + mypy)
make test           # Run pytest across all Python repos

# ─── Environment activation ───────────────────────────────────────────────
source activate.sh && source ~/.exodus/env.local

# ─── Development (from repo roots) ────────────────────────────────────────
uv run pytest tests/ -v
uv run ruff check .
uv run mypy . --ignore-missing-imports
sqlfluff lint dbt-framework/models/ --dialect databricks
terraform fmt -check -recursive
pre-commit run --all-files

# ─── IronLayer CLI ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ironlayer plan          # Generate validated execution plan
ironlayer diff          # Schema / data diff
ironlayer lineage       # Lineage query
ironlayer status        # System health check

# ─── Exodus Autopilot CLI ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
exodus review code <path>       # AI code review (local first)
exodus agent run --item <ID>    # Run backlog item interactively
exodus agent run --next         # Run highest-priority item
exodus ai-usage                 # Track Anthropic spend
exodus monitor schema           # Check bronze table schema drift
```

## AI Configuration — Single Source of Truth

**CRITICAL: Never edit AI configs directly in individual repos.**
Always edit in `ai/cursor/rules/`, `ai/claude/skills/`, etc., then run `make sync-ai`.

```
ai/cursor/rules/          → synced to .cursor/rules/ in all active repos
ai/cursor/skills/         → synced to .cursor/skills/ in all active repos
ai/cursor/mcp.json.template → synced to .cursor/mcp.json in all active repos
ai/claude/CLAUDE.md       → synced to CLAUDE.md in all active repos
ai/claude/skills/         → synced to .claude/skills/ in all active repos
ai/shared/AGENTS.md       → synced to AGENTS.md in all active repos
```

## Repo-Specific Overrides

Each repo can have a `local-rules/` directory with overrides NOT managed by sync.
Use for repo-specific conventions that don't apply workspace-wide.

## Version Management

- Workspace version: `workspace.yml` (semver — bump when standards change)
- Tool versions: `.tool-versions` (mise pins — all developers use same versions)
- Product versions: semver tags in each product repo

## Environment Setup

```bash
# Credentials live in ~/.exodus/env.local (never commit)
# Template at: tooling/env/env.template
# Load with: source ~/.exodus/env.local
```

Key env vars: `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `DATABRICKS_HOST`, `DATABRICKS_TOKEN`, `GITHUB_TOKEN`, `EXODUS_BUDGET_LIMIT`, `OLLAMA_BASE_URL`
